    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.23.11h-11k_0004"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">11ga <del>27</del></fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">MEMBER:</hi> <hi rend="italics">National Association of Insurance Agents
                    
                    California State Association of Insurance Agents</hi>
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>An Eagle Perched Atop a Shield</figDesc>
                        <p><unclear/> NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF INSURANCE AGENTS</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">OXFORD 4-3314
                    308 BANK OF AMERICA BLDG.</hi>
                    
                    <hi rend="italics">National Association of Accident and Health Underwriters</hi>
                    <hi rend="caps">W.H.H. PILCHER
                    <hi rend="italic">IN WHITTIER SINCE 1920</hi>
                    =========================================
                    INSURE AND FEEL SECURE</hi>
                    
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>Whittier Insurance Exchange Seal</figDesc>
                        <p>THE SIGN OF GOOD INSURANCE  WHITTIER INSURANCE EXCHANGE</p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">WHITTIER
                    CALIFORNIA</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <note type="recipient">ansd</note>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 17, 1952</dateline>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Mr. John <hi rend="caps">G.</hi> Neihardt,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>University of Missouri,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Columbia, Missouri.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>Dear John:</salute> 
                </opener>
                <p>This will come as a surprise to you since you have perhaps given no thought to my name for more than a half century. While vacationing in Arizona a few weeks ago I picked up a book at a Trading Post and since the title indicated that it dealt with a Sioux boy I was somewhat intrigued. Upon looking inside the cover I found that you were the author.</p>
                
                <p>Many years have passed since you and I were together on the Omaha reservation. I believe that I last saw you in 1899 or perhaps 1900 I remember you very distinctly. It is gratifying to know that you have done so much with your literary talent. I recall when you were starting out as a reporter for the Bancroft Blade. I have just finished re-reading your"Song of the Indian Wars" which I have en<del>n</del><add>j</add>oyed so much.</p>
                
                <p>After leaving school<del>I</del>I discovered that I had a flair for selling and have been engaged in some form of it ever since. During the past 20 years I have been engaged in the General Insurance business in this city. My principal avocation has been in connection with Indians for whom I have never lost my affection. As a dire<del>f</del><add>c</add>tor of the National Congress of American Indians I keep in close contact with the affairs of Indians nation-wide.</p>
                
                <p>I made my first visit to the Omaha reservation in 30 years last July. It was distressing to find that most of the older folks were gone to their Happy Hunting Ground. In talking with a few that I used to know I was quite surprised to learn that I had not forgtten the Omaha language. My sister Etta Brownrigg, and I are the only ones left of the Pilcher faction.</p> 
                
                <p>Although your address is uncertain I hope that this letter will reach you and that it may soon have a reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most cordially,</salute>
                    <signed><unclear/> Pilcher</signed>
                    <signed>W.H.H. Pilcher.</signed>
                    <signed>"omphaghinga"</signed>
                
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>326 <hi rend="caps">S.</hi> Pickering Ave.,</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Whittier, Calif.</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
                <fw type="letterhead"><hi rend="italics">Representing Only Old Line Stock Insurance Companies</hi></fw>
                
            </div1>
